1. main idea is to use inorder traversal because it will keep the order of values.

Morris Traversal
```
public void recoverTree(TreeNode root) {
        TreeNode previous = null;
        TreeNode first = null;
        TreeNode second = null;
        // binary tree inorder traversal iteratively
        TreeNode parent = null;
        TreeNode current = root;
        while (current != null) {
            if (current.left != null) {
                parent = current.left;
                while (parent.right != null && parent.right != current) {
                    parent = parent.right;
                }
                if (parent.right == null) {
                    parent.right = current;
                    current = current.left;
                    continue;
                } else {
                    parent.right = null;
                }
            }
            if (previous != null) {
                if (previous.val > current.val) {
                    if (first == null) {
                        first = previous;
                    }
                    second = current;
                }
            }
            previous = current;
            current = current.right;
        }
        // swap value
        final int temp = first.val;
        first.val = second.val;
        second.val = temp;
    }
```

2. Recursive Inorder Traversal
