# Intuition
-  We will traverse the tree in inorder fashion and check whether previous node had value less than the root.
- If yes, than note both of them.
- After the traversal we  will simply, swap both the nodes.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(n) (Stack space for recursion)

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    private TreeNode prev = null , first = null , sec = null;
    public void recoverTree(TreeNode root) {
        helper(root);
        swap(first , sec);
        return;
    }
    private void swap (TreeNode a , TreeNode b){
        int temp = a.val;
        a.val = b.val;
        b.val = temp;
    }
    private void helper (TreeNode root){
        if(root == null)
        return;

        helper(root.left);

        if(prev != null && prev.val > root.val){
            if(first == null)
                first = prev;
            sec = root;
        }

        prev = root;

        helper(root.right);
    }
}
```

