The Solution is Based on a observation that,
1. Since Inorder traversal gives sorted order, so we start looking from smaller values to larger values and hence we first get bigger part of the swapped integers
2. once we get the bigger part that is when x,y,z and x<y and y>z then we are sure that we need to remove y from this position
3. Henceforth we start finding a smaller value 
