In the question, we do inorder traversal and find out the wrong placed numbers and there are two cases for that:
(i) both nodes are adjacent and hence there wont be third number wrong placed.
(ii)otherwise, if a number is misplaced, it's next element will also seem to be mispalced as we're checking with parent node. hence we store both parent and root as first and middle.

We'll swap first and last if both nodes are separated or will swap first and middle if both nodes are adjacent.
