If we do traversal(here inorder) in the tree and store the values in an arraylist and sort the arraylist, we can get the right tree after inserting the sorted values in the tree again by inorder traversal.
```
//Doing inorderTraversal in the tree and then storing it in an arraylist and then sorting the list and again inserting the sorted values in the tree by doing inorder traversal.
class Solution {
    ArrayList<Integer> list=new ArrayList<>();
    int count=0;
    public void recoverTree(TreeNode root) {
        inorder(root);
        Collections.sort(list); // Sorting the list 
        insertinorder(root);

    }
    public void inorder(TreeNode root){
        if(root==null){
            return;
        }
        inorder(root.left);
        list.add(root.val); // Adding to the list
        inorder(root.right);
    }
	public void insertinorder(TreeNode root){
        if(root==null){
            return;
        }
        insertinorder(root.left);
        root.val=list.get(count); // Changing the value of the node as per the sorted list
        count++;
        insertinorder(root.right);
    }
}
