Recursive DFS solution (Accepted 0ms):
```
/*
Keeping track of depth, i.e when going to a child node, increase depth and when coming back, decrease depth.
At each new level (depth), add the rightmost node to the answer list.
Since we go to the **right child first** and then the left, when we arrive on a new level **for the first time**, we shall always arrive at the rightmost node.
*/
class Solution {

    int depth = 0;
    List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

    public List<Integer> rightSideView(TreeNode root) {

        if(root == null)
            return ans;

        depth++;

        if (ans.size() < depth)
            ans.add(root.val);

        ans = rightSideView(root.right);
        ans = rightSideView(root.left);

        depth--;

        return ans;
    }
}
```

Iterative BFS solution (without changing the signature of question, Accepted 1ms) :
```
class Solution {

    public List<Integer> rightSideView(TreeNode root) {

        // create array to store answer
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        // check for edge case
        if (root == null)
            return ans;

        // make queue to store the nodes breadth first, add root
        Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();

        queue.add(root);
        queue.add(null); // a null indicates that the current level has ended, the next level begin from next node in the queue

        while (queue.size() != 0)
        {
            // get the first element from queue
            TreeNode cur = queue.remove();

            // if we get null, move to next level, check if queue is empty else it will result in infinite loop
            if (cur == null)
            {
                if (queue.size() == 0)
                    break;

                queue.add(null);
            }

            else
            {
                // the last element of each level (the element before null) will be seen from the right side
                if (queue.peek() == null)
                    ans.add(cur.val);

                // add the children of current element in queue, as part of the next level
                if (cur.left != null)
                    queue.add(cur.left);

                if (cur.right != null)
                    queue.add(cur.right);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

