We need the rightmost entry of each level. Since we go level-by-level it is BFS.
One thing is, we only want to add the last element of each level. Traverse the nodes from right-to-left and store the depth of each node. Add a node to answer only if its depth is larger than the maximum depth observed so far, i.e. `d > prev_d` below.

```python
from collections import deque
class Solution:
    def rightSideView(self, root):
        if not root: return []

        ans = []
        que = deque([(root, 0)])
        prev_d = -1
        while que:
            node, d = que.popleft()
            if node.right: que.append((node.right, d+1))
            if node.left: que.append((node.left, d+1))
            if d>prev_d: ans.append(node.val)
            prev_d = d
        return ans
```

