# Intution
    We will use DFS instead of BFS because it is more space optimized.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

    We will Traverse through root->right->left unlike trivial
    pre-order traversal which is root->left->right.

    Whenever the traversal level equals to ans size, we push the root 
    value in ans, which will be right View.

    Similarly for left view we can use trivial PreOrder Traversal i.e,
    root->left->right.

    Go through the code for more clear concept.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
      void helper(TreeNode* root,vector<int>&ans,int level){
        if(root== NULL)
        return;
        if(ans.size() == level){
            ans.push_back(root->val);
        }
        helper(root->right,ans,level+1);
        helper(root->left,ans,level+1);
    }
    vector<int> rightSideView(TreeNode* root) {
        vector<int>ans;
        int level = 0;
        helper(root,ans,level);
        return ans;
    }
};
```
