Order of Traversal => root -> right -> left
For each level(height) maintain a map, to check if we have taken a node from this level or not.
The order of our traversal ensures that we visit rightmost node at any level first. Push that node in answer vector and mark that level as visited or 1.
**Recursive implementation of the above idea**:
```
class Solution {
public:
    map<int, int> m;
    vector<int> ans;
    void rec(TreeNode *root, int h) {
        if(root == NULL) return;
        if(m[h] == 0) {
            ans.push_back(root -> val);
            m[h] = 1;
        }
        rec(root -> right, h + 1);
        rec(root -> left, h + 1);
    }
    vector<int> rightSideView(TreeNode* root) {
        rec(root, 0);
        return ans;
    }
};
```

